parameters: (...Let's stop by Oei-san's dumpling shop before going in.)

(...Come to think of it, I haven't checked the town
bulletin... I should talk to the bulletin board owner near
my home.)

Marunouchi is the vanguard protecting Edo Castle. Naturally,
the security is strict. If you don't want to be suspected,
it's best to return to the town.
Please line up in two rows! And no pushing!

Many are disheartened because we couldn't protect our lord
and the castle.

The current Shogun-sama is a capable person. We, the
shogunate retainers, can't afford to be careless.

I heard that the notorious thief was caught by the
magistrate's office. They say he's been exiled to Mujou
Island, so he likely won't be returning to Edo anymore.

A notice has been issued for the samurai lords living in Edo
to enter the castle armed. It seems many are confused
because the purpose is unclear.

How bold of you to show up at the magistrate's office so
casually. As expected of the former master thief, Nezumi
Komachi, huh?
...! (Ugh, maybe I shouldn't have come here...)

Don't be so wary. A directive has come from Lord Shinana of
the council of elders. Nezumi Komachi has been exonerated,
and from now on, you are free to do as you please--

Indeed. We have been ordered to dispose of all records of
Nezumi Komachi's crimes and disturbances. The magistrate's
office will no longer pursue you.

Well, to be honest, it's quite bitter for us who have been
run ragged by you.

After your capture, we thoroughly searched your home. We
thought you might be hiding a chest of a thousand ry, but
not a single koban was found. So you really scattered all
the stolen koban throughout Edo, didn't you?

...My father who went by the name Nezumi Koz did the same,
and I simply followed in his footsteps. It's not something
to be praised for.

Ha ha ha! Don't be so modest. There are plenty of thieves in
the world who are called righteous outlaws, but most steal
out of their own greed. A thief as incorruptible and honest
as your father is rare. I'm impressed.

You turned yourself in because you were thinking about my
granddaughter Omitsu, weren't you?

...Because I heard that grandpa was going to commit seppuku.
I couldn't stand by and do nothing...

That's why I can trust you. Karin, you must already know
this, but from now on, what is required of you is to protect
Edo.

You have the guts to return from Mujou Island. With the
resolve to make amends for the trouble you've caused the
magistrate's office, fulfill your upcoming duties with
honor, understand?

So you're heading to Fuji. Please take care of Yugiri-dono.
Good luck in battle--

This is the magistrate's office. Working day and night for
the peace of Edo's citizens.
The magistrate's office is busy. Please make it brief.

Reports of ogre sightings have been increasing at the
magistrate's office. I never thought we'd actually have to
fight a real ogre... Chasing after Nezumi Komachi was better
than this.

The demons were not foes that could be defeated with the
likes of a sasumata. It's frustrating, but it's fair to say
it was our complete defeat. How regrettable...

...What is this mansion, you ask? It's not for a town girl
like you to know. Hurry on home.

This place was once a plaza where soldiers would gather in
times of emergency. Now that it's a peaceful era, many pine
trees have been planted and it has become a park.

The magistrate's office seems busy too. Just when I thought
the rat problem was over, now there's been a kidnapping
incident, and they're working without any days off, it
seems.

Being a poor samurai family, we sold our armor quite some
time ago, so this new directive is quite the problem... I
must procure some armor from somewhere! Oh dear...!

This is an important treasury. I will not allow anyone to
intrude inside.

Oh no...! All the treasure chests inside the treasury have
been stolen...! Wha-what should we do...!?

"If you find the thief Nezumi Komachi, report it immediately
--Magistrate's Office"

Huh--!? (There's a wanted poster for Nezumi Komachi on the
magistrate's office signboard!)

...(Yeah... It's okay. It doesn't look like me... I can't
see myself in it)

Numerous burglary incidents by a duo of brothers. Report
immediately to the magistrate's office if spotted--

Due to an emergency situation, going outside is prohibited--
protect yourselves accordingly. By order of the magistrate's
office.

It's been half a year since the former boss was killed by a
demon... Yugiri-dono has taken over as the head and is
diligently carrying out her duties, but the organization is
short-staffed. I have high hopes for you, Karin-dono.

Oh? Weren't you supposed to go to Suranashi Village with
Yugiri-dono? Yugiri-dono hasn't returned here, has she?

Ogres are appearing all around the outskirts of Edo. It's as
if they've coordinated this...

It is a matter of extreme regret that we could not protect
the castle and our lord... With many of the Iga ninja
injured, we have no choice but to entrust our fate to you
all.

The townspeople are in a panic since Edo Castle burned down.
We must defeat the chief of the demons to bring peace to the
world. I will definitely win, Karin--

It's been a while since I took out the armor from the
storehouse and put it on, but I wonder if this is right...

Even the Edo bannerets have been called upon. It seems to be
an order from the elder councilor. What could be the matter
that they're gathering soldiers in this peaceful Edo...

I was being attacked by demons, and I thank you for your
help. So you Iga ninjas have been fighting such monsters in
secret. I acknowledge your hardships.

Karin? Half of the officials at the magistrate's office are
injured and receiving treatment at the clinic... We're
declaring martial law and urging the people of Edo to stay
in their homes.

Omitsu, be at ease. I am unharmed. Stay at home until things
settle down. Understood?
Grandpa, are you okay!? Are you hurt!?
